-Earths into pre-dominantly rocky ones that have radii below $\\sim 1.5\nR_\\oplus$, and ones that still retain a substantial atmosphere and/or volatile\ncomponents, and have radii above $\\sim 2 R_\\oplus$. That the less heavily\nirradiated of the 3 planets still retains an atmosphere, may indicate that\nphotoevaporation has played a key role in the evolution of the planets in this\nsystem.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 18 Dec 2018 11:18:16 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 21 Dec 2018 11:35:46 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 11 Jan 2019 15:37:49 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-01-23"}
